<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n37009q"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n37" href="#n37009q">N37 (VI.B.28A)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n37all.htm#n37009q"> 9(q)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 322 Charming old lady</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[<font size="-1">THE CIRCUS</font>]</font>: In his advance notes for 1879 Barnum wrote: &ldquo;One <mark>charming old lady</mark> in Boston, with a troop of happy grandchildren in her train, shook me cordially by the hand and, with a face beaming with smiles, said to me: &ldquo;Oh, Mr. Barnum, I don&apos;t know how to thank you enough for the pleasure you have afforded these darlings <font color="green">[in your Museum and Managerie]</font>. &hellip;&rdquo; <small> M.R. Werner, <a name="MRWP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MRWP"><cite title="source">P.T. Barnum</cite></a> (1923) 322</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
